<ol>
<li>
<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
    @HI{{@KJ{{tall^mountain}}sanha @KJ{{day^book^person}} @EM{{ni shite ha}} @KJ{{large}}kiidesu.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
    Mr. Takayama is big for a Japanese person.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
<li>
<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
    @HI{{@KT{{bobu}}ha @KJ{{day^book^word}}wo yoku @KJ{{exertion^strong}}shite iru @EM{{ni shita ha}} @KJ{{below^hand}}desu.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
    Considering that Bob is studying Japanese hard, he is poor at it.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
<li>
<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
    @HI{{@KJ{{he}}ha @KT{{resura-}} datta @EM{{ni shite ha}} @KJ{{body}}ga@KJ{{little}}sai.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
    Considering that he was a wrestler, he is small.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</ol>

<h2> Notes </h2>

@HI{{@EM{{ni shite ha}}}} is the @HI{{te}}-form of @HI{{ni suru}} and literally means "if one makes it ~".
